Task:
Using only HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, create a browser-based desktop operating system simulation that runs entirely in the browser.

Core Requirements:

The entire project must be contained in one self-contained file (single HTML script with embedded CSS and JS).

The file must be directly openable in any modern web browser with no external dependencies, libraries, or servers.

Features (Minimum 5 Total Applications/Functions):

A desktop-style user interface with draggable application windows.

Two fully functional, playable games (keyboard and/or mouse controlled).

A wallpaper management feature allowing the user to change the desktop background at runtime.

A Zero-Gravity Desktop Mode where windows float, drift, or animate as if in low gravity space.

A Calculator able to function.

add additional creative utility or application of your choice (e.g., notes app, system settings, clock, 2048 game, etc.).

Design & Behavior Constraints:

No external assets required (optional placeholders allowed).

All UI logic, animations, and interactions must be handled with vanilla JavaScript.

The experience should feel like a lightweight operating system, not just a webpage.

Deliverable:

Provide the complete single-file source code ready to save as an .html file and run locally.
